title: Recruitment Specialist
twitter: I have a skill of people management and most of my background is in international business.I really came into HR Recruitment field in 2012 without knowing that I had done an HR job since 2009 in USA. I learned how to do an interview, how to select candidates and how to train them when I was an assistant manager at Panda Restaurant Group. I had done all of those with Panara Bread in USA as well. Thus, my experience with recruitment is about four years. I feel recruitment is charming because I need several skill to match people with a job. And, it is challenging as I also need a hunting skill.I believe as a recruiter I have a chance to help many people to find them self and company to learn what to improve. twitter: For the latest career, I worked as a Customer Relationship Assistant Manager and Sales channel enhancement at Bank of Ayudhya Public Company Limited. I have extensive experience in the field of computer engineering, information system, and business analysis. Since I started out my career as a BI consultant I gradually moved toward business sections after completing my MBA degree, then have been involved in both technical and business project management concentrating on strategic planning and market data analysis with various companies, including Krung Thai AXA. Experienced with external and internal clients for various business industries provided marketing-solution-focused, trend analysis and transcribe results from data analysis into strategic plan for sales improvement and workforce management. My clients include large and medium sized companies and Government Sectors, e.g., Thaioil Group, Sansiri Group, The Prime Minister’s Office Thailand, Ministry of Energy, Provincial Electricity Authority, Food and Drug Administration, Department of Medical Sciences Ministry of Public Health, and BPB Thai gypsum.Successful Business Leadership & Management As a project manager I leaded team to success and managed both technical consulting project and strategic planning project. I had delivered successes improvement in clients insurance claim process, develop retaining customers plan and enrich remuneration for distributor channels as a manager in strategic planning at AXA. While in Bank of Ayudhya I implemented reward and recognition programs in order to escalate sales and also providing cross sales opportunities via new channels such as Internet banking, SMS, E-mail system and Krungsri Mobile application.

summary: From 2004 to 2010, Raimon Land has completed eight properties worth a total sales value of over THB 12 billion: four in central Bangkok (under three brand names: The Lofts, The Lakes and The Legend), two in Pattaya (Northshore and Northpoint) and two in Phuket (Kata Gardens and The Heights Phuket).Going forward, Raimon Land intends to maintain the rapid pace of growth set in recent years. The company will continue to proactively identify new opportunities and negotiate land acquisitions for future developments specializing in a wide array of offerings for virtually every walk of life including mid-to-high-end condominiums, niche town house and villa projects as well as a newly launched brand called UNIXX that will bring Raimon Land quality to the entry level segment in Bangkok and resort areas.The company currently has a portfolio of four on-going projects and a number of planned future projects on the horizon. With the THB 5 billion Northpoint property in Pattaya completed in 2010, from 2012 to 2014, Raimon Land will hand over residential properties including The River and 185 Rajadamri, both located in Bangkok as well as Pattaya's Zire Wongamat and the newly launched Unixx South Pattaya. With a total sales value worth over THB 31 billion when accounting for the new lifestyle retail development The Vue, Raimon Land is well positioned for the future.

title: Corporate Communications| Marketing Communications| Marketing Management| PR
twitter: 16 years of professional experiences, 9 years of Corporate Communications Profile at Bangkok Glass and 7 years of Marketing & Sales Background.Bangkok Glass Group of Companies is a leading total packaging solutions manufacturer in Thailand and South East Asia. We supply everyday's life containers, which are glass containers, plastic crates, caps, closures, and corrugated carton boxes to those leading bottler, pharmaceutical, and food & beverages producers. Besides, being a leader in container manufacturing company, we are concerning in social responsibility. We are implementing various of recycling projects as well as sport sponsorships. One of the outstanding mission is establishing a professional football club named 'Bangkok Glass Football Club' or 'BGFC'. The club has a mission to upgrade Thai's professional football career and support the Pathumthani Province's community. As a corporate communications manager, I take full responsibilities in Bangkok Glass Group's corporate communications and public relations (PR)); overseeing corporate images, positions, and messages to create consistent communications; defining communications plans and strategies to drive effective-and-efficient corporate presences and visibility in public exposures.I am also in charge of BGFC branding, public relations and commercial; business directions, marketing and product plans into PR and communications strategies.. As the club must be sustainable, bringing income and creating market opportunities for the club is necessary.The position was also responsible for leading Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) as well as crisis and issue management roles

title: Digital Transformation Executive - Telco, Media & Entertainment, Asia Pacific at IBM
twitter: Stephen Kerwick currently holds the position of Asia Pacific Solution Sales Leader, Digital Transformation - Telecom, Media & Entertainment at IBM. He leverages his industry knowledge and experience to help telecommunications customers understand their mobile subscriber data via IBM's rich analytics product portfolio. He also heads up Digital Transformation with specific emphasis on Customer Insight and Omni channel Digital Experience Industry solutions. He has pioneered mobile market segmentation by leveraging a mix of analytics and data mining to understand and predict subscriber behavior. His background includes more than 15 years of sales, operations, strategy consulting and professional services in mobile analytics and business intelligence. Prior to IBM, he was Vice President, Asia Pacific & Middle East at both comScore and Neuralitic Systems. He has also held executive level positions at Cisco Systems, Openwave Systems, SPSS, BroadVision, and DoubleClick Inc. In these positions he was responsible for building the mobile analytics and predictive analytics practices and product lines. Mr. Kerwick began his career with Accenture upon completing a successful career in the United States Army.He is also a notable international speaker and Asia Pacific expert within the telecommunications and media industries. He is a sought after industry expert and thought leader who uses advanced techniques to increase subscriber adoption and ARPU and overall VAS revenues. Mr. Kerwick graduated with a Bachelor of Science, General Engineering and a Bachelor of Science, Literature from the United States Military Academy at West Point. Stephen is fluent in German and conversant in Thai and Tagalog.        See lessSee less of undefined summary

twitter: A holistic communication agency executive sharpened with intensive marketing experience more than 12 years. Have a full passion in learning new things and making things happen. Is well-rounded with integrated communication planning and execution. With a background on plenty of critical businesses, i.e. Budweisers, Beck's, Vinasoy, Samsung, Watsons, Singha Park Chiang Rai, Reckitt Benckiser – Nurofen, Gaviscon, Senokot for PR & Activations launch campaign, ME By TMB new banking Corporate Branding & launch, Mead Johnsons for Enfa brandrepositioning , P&G (Corporate Campaign, Downy, Pampers, SK-II, Olay, Pantene, Rejoice, etc), McDonald’s, adidas, and Richemonde (Johnnie Walker, Smirnoff, etc.). Have developed not only a strategic thinking but also creative solutions for variety of client briefs. Pleasure fashion, cosmetics, music, and traveling. And, aim to be an expert in holistic marketing communication executives.Experienced in marketing world for almost 3 years with Shell Oil Product East, the regional marketing department for Shell Asia located in Thailand.  I was responsible for the retail marketing in growing the business for both fuel and lubricant products in this region. title: SAP Consultant at Atos
twitter: I worked as SAP Change Management Consultant for Atos, Thailand. Previously, I was working as Consultant for SAP Successfactors (Human Resources Management Systems on the Cloud).I tend to believe that I have a good general grip on my professional career however there are still many gaps that I would like to fill while working in a challenging work environment.I am convinced that being an optimistic, enthusiastic and systematic thinker is not only a theoretical qualification of a so called "best worker". For me, these virtues are essential to create value and long term success. Furthermore, moving occasionally out of one’s comfort zone, meeting people with different background and from different cultures are also important factors for me to become successful.       I am a Bachelor of Arts, major in German language and minor in Accounting from Thammasat University, Bangkok, Thailand. In my spare time, I enjoy reading German novels from Goethe and Schiller and I admire Nietzsche and his philosophy. On the weekends, I play piano and violin and go swimming to keep fit. summary: Alex is a software engineer architect specializing in enterprise technologies, test automation  and continuous delivery based on the Java platform. He has over a decade of experience in the Java world, yet continually renews his skill set by learning new aptitudes and technologies every day.Alex believes in the open source software model, free software, and open standards and how they can help companies to delivery software faster and safer. He is the leader of NoSQLUnit, member of JSR374 Expert Group and team member of Arquillian, Asciidoctor and Tomitribe (Apache TomEE).Alex has contributed to DZone site, TheServerSide web, Methods and Tools magazine and RebelLabs blog. Moreover he is an international speaker, presenting his talks at software conferences like Devoxx (2011, 2012), LinuxTag, Puppet BaseCamp, Barcelona JUG, Codemotion (2013, 2014), Guatemala JavaDays (2013-2014), JavaLand, GeeCon or SpringIO.Alex is currently cowriting Arquillian in Action for Manning with Jason Porter, and he is also the curator of lordofthejars.com blog (awarded with DZone Most-Valuable-Blog), a place to talk about Java world. In his free time, he spends time with his wife and daughters.

title: International Tax Senior Advisor at KPMG
twitter: Karn is an international tax specialist at KPMG Thailand, focusing on multi-jurisdiction tax restructuring, M&A tax for inbound and outbound investments, and tax planning for cross-border transactions.He has provided tax advices to multinational corporations and Thai listed companies on wide range of tax-efficient strategies. He has experiences of tax planning involving many countries: Singapore, Hong Kong, Thailand, Malaysia, Indonesia, BVI, the Cayman Islands and Mauritius. He represents clients to negotiate with tax authorities on tax investigation and tax refund cases.He also has a background as an auditor (CPA) of KPMG Thailand, providing audit services for clients in telecommunication, electronics and FMCG industries. twitter: Two-and-a-half-year work experience as an ASEAN equity analyst in one of the biggest funds in Thailand plus four-year work experience in auditing area (Audit Associate and Senior Auditor) in high-profile domestic and international organisations which involved combining strong analytical skills on financial reports with business and internal control wisdom of various business sectors.  Excellent interpersonal, teamwork and leadership skills complemented with outstanding communication skills in English and co-ordinating ability under multinational working environment are what I have from working in ASEAN investment team and in PwC.# Key Strengths:   Experience in ASEAN investment as an equity analyst at BBL Asset Management Co.,Ltd. for almost 3 years.      Sound academic knowledge of accounting and finance (merit grade @ Top 5 UK Business School)      4 years of first-class accounting experience at PwC complemented with CPA certificate (assistant  auditor and senior consultant)      Excellent leadership and teamwork skills (led group of 20 people at PwC)      International exposure and strong clients network (developed longstanding relationship with both domestic and overseas PwC clients)      Quickly adaptable to new business situations (worked in a fast-paced and challenging environment)      Excellent communication skills in English and Thai# Expertise:   Financial analysis   Corporate finance   Accounting (IFRS, US GAAP and Thai GAAP)   Auditing   Consulting# Seeking:   Full-time position in finance and consulting in Singapore and Thailand        See lessSee less of undefined summary

title: Internet Intrapreneur - Transforming the way companies grow their business while having fun doing it!
twitter: Seasoned intrepreneur who has deep understanding of technology startup with several years of experience in project management and team building from scratch. Problem solver with “get things done” attitude, “making a positive impact” motivation and ability to both lead at high level and hands-on as result-orientation needed Korpong gained his bachelor and began his career as an account executive at Groupon, the world fastest-growing company. He moved to join The Stock Exchange of Thailand as project lead to build the first investment learning centre in Thailand meanwhile studied his MBA. After that he in-house rotated to join Market for alternative investment "NASDQ of Thailand" as a business analyst to lead startup ecosystem development project from day 1 and craft startup support scheme to uplift Thai startup. Now, he is transforming the accounting landscape as a business development manager with Thailand largest cloud accounting software company - FlowAccountKorpong speaks fluent English and Thai, and elementary GermanSpecialities : Business Development, Sales Management, Startup Performance Management, Project Management, Digital Analytics, Business Model Design, Community BuildingFeel free to add me to your network at korpong@me.com or call me at +66-867-577-225More info:- my bio: http://bit.ly/KorpongBio- my blog: http://bit.ly/KorpongBlog- my presentations: http://bit.ly/tumkt27oct

summary: Tithirat is an experienced Chief Information Security Officer with more than 16 years of progressive responsibility in information security, IT risk management, cyber security strategy, governance, regulatory compliance and business continuity management. Tithirat calibrated security challenges across people, technology, business and processes to ensure adherence and compliance.Holding her CISM, CObIT, CISSP, CRISC, CGEIT, PCI ISA, PCIP and ISO 27001 LA certificates, Tithirat’s career has expanded across Insurance, Banking and Telecommunication industries. She currently serves as Chief Information Security Officer for Krungthai-AXA Life Insurance, directing the security operations and management for the organization to ensure the execution of information security and leading security implementation programmes in Asia region. title: COO at Nikos Logistics Co., Ltd.
twitter: The steep rise of labor cost in South East Asia has put pressure on the region to maintain price competitiveness. In Thailand only, from 2001 to 2011, the wages have increased by 49% offsetting manufacturing industry’s local advantages. Supply chain and logistics need now more than ever to develop their workforce skills and competencies while improving manufacturing productivity. New systems need to be created, implemented and integrated to bring back the region’s attractiveness. Now the solution may be great but it does not ensure employees acceptance and hence, performance improvement. What will consolidate the outcome is how people will embrace the change. This is where I come in. I ease the transition from a previous model to a new model. I am a Thai-French Change Management consultant with an IT background and 5 years experience in both SMEs and multinationals in Europe and South East Asia. I have a broad comprehension of businesses needs and constraints and am able to develop innovative methods that do not only solve issues but leverage businesses activities. As a matter of fact, I have implemented from Purchase to Pay systems to shop floor systems and Warehouse management systems. I analyze client’s process performance, identify areas of improvement and provide practical guidance to the decisional and operational teams, ensuring a successful implementation.
